&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Trust Specialist Registrar in Endocrinology (Ealing) Fixed Term - Until Aug 22 (renewable)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is recruiting to a Trust Specialist Registrar post in Endocrinology/GIM. The post will be based at Ealing Hospital, and it would be an ideal starting point for someone looking to apply for SpR training schemes in endocrinology and diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be expected to contribute to the ongoing care of general medicine inpatients on the wards .The diabetes and endocrinology team has 20-40 inpatients and the designated ward for the team is 6 North. Inpatient care is supported by two SpR’s from the NW London training scheme and this trust post, a core medical trainee, a GP VTS doctor and three foundation year doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will also be opportunities for the post holder to partake in outpatient clinics and undertake audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will receive the full support of the department to fulfil their training requirements and develop special interests. Specific examples include diabetic foot clinics, imaging techniques in benign thyroid disease, observation of radio-iodine therapy, insulin pump clinics and clinical database analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Kevin Baynes - Clinical Lead Endocrinology - kevin.baynes@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
